.says its,illegal From Stanley Uzoaru, Owerri The Nigeria Association of Zoological Gardens and Wildlife Park (NAZAP) said it would reverse the relocation of the animals from the Imo State zoological garden to Jos. President of the association, Dipo Bali who disclosed this to Daily Sun on Sunday said the purported relocation of the animals is illegal,maintaining that NAZAP and the ministry of of environment was not consulted. According to him,animals are not just relocated or transported unless they meet the necessary conditions of the bodies concerned.